\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 CopperExport for iPhoto\
Version [[version]]
\fs24 \

\f1\b0 [[date]].\
\
CopperExport for iPhoto is a plugin for iPhoto 4 through 7 which allows you to export pictures directly into a Coppermine gallery (http://coppermine.sf.net/). It is a universal binary.\
\
See the ChangeLog file for a detailed list of changes.\
\

\f0\b\fs28 \ul Installation
\f1\b0 \

\fs24 \ulnone \
1. Double click on the CopperExport.pkg package file.\
2. Follow the instructions of the installer.\
3. 
\f0\b Important: 
\f1\b0 Apply the server-side configuration (see below) to be able to set photo titles, descriptions and keywords.\

\f0\b \ul \

\fs28 System Requirements
\f1\b0 \

\fs24 \ulnone \
CopperExport for iPhoto requires Mac OS X 10.3 or later and iPhoto 4.x-7.x.  iPhoto 2.x 
\f2\i may
\f1\i0  work, but has not been tested (please let me know if you do).  Versions of Mac OS X prior to 10.3 will certainly not work.\
\
It has been tested with Coppermine 1.3.2, 1.3.3, and 1.4.x. Older versions may work, but have not been tested. See the notes below on optional (but recommended) server-side configuration.\
\
