\f3\i The longer explanation:\

\f0\i0 \

\f1\b0 CopperExport uses the existing "Windows XP export wizard" interface in Coppermine. Unfortunately, in the default distribution of Coppermine, this interface does not accept additional information like the title, description and keywords for a picture, or the description for new albums. If you have access to your Coppermine installation directory (through shell of FTP access to your web server), you can make some small changes to the xp_publish.php file in Coppermine to enable this functionality.\
\

\f2\i If you cannot do not have the possibility of making these changes, you can still upload files, but the caption, description and keywords will not be applied, or the description for new albums.\

\f1\i0 \
In the cpg-patches folder of the CopperExport disk image, you will find the appropriate files. Follow the instructions above to install the necessary changes.\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \
The changes to 
\f4 xp_publish.php
\f1  do not affect the capability of uploading things from Windows XP.
